notes: Goodwin's 112* represented his highest ever score in One-Day Internationals. His previous best was 111 v Sri Lanka at Colombo in 1997-98

Zimbabwe's victory provided it with its highest ever score when batting second in a One-Day International. The team's previous record stood at 278, a mark reached against Australia in Delhi in 1997-98

milestones.description: Grant Flower and Goodwin's 186-run partnership is ZIM's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 145 between Andy Waller and Andy Flower
Campbell has broken the record for most catches (47) in ODIs for ZIM, going past Grant Flower's 46
This is the highest match aggregate (577) involving teams West Indies & Zimbabwe in ODIs
Dirk Viljoen has conceded the most runs in an innings (75) in ODIs for ZIM, going past Eddo Brandes's record of 74
Grant Flower and Goodwin's 186-run partnership is ZIM's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 161 between Grant Flower and Andy Flower

stories.title: 7th Match, Zimbabwe v West Indies, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1616th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Roger Harper admits West Indies confidence needs a boost
stories.summary:
West Indies face an uphill battle to restore the confidence needed to fend
off England in the remaining Cornhill Tests after being knocked out of the
NatWest Series by Zimbabwe at Chester Le Street today

stories.title: Extraordinary fightback wipes out West Indies' hopes
stories.summary:
An extraordinary fightback from Zimbabwe enabled them to pull off an amazing
victory over West Indies by six wickets

stories.title: Zimbabwe's astonishing victory in magnificent match
stories.summary: Will the real Zimbabwe cricket team please stand up

stories.title: Exciting finish in prospect - Tall task for Zimbabwe
stories.summary:
Riverside, 30 overs: West Indies 287 for five (50 overs); Zimbabwe 145 for
four (Goodwin 58, G Flower 18)

stories.title: West Indies take strong grip and Lara's still there
stories.summary:
West Indies took a strong grip on the NatWest Series match against Zimbabwe
with some fine batting in the first 30 overs after winning the toss on an
excellent batting pitch

stories.title: Big Victory needed at Chester-le-Street
stories.summary:
This match is contested by two teams who have both suffered crushing defeats
at the hands of the resurgent England side during the past few days
